other_tests.findings: No evidence of bony injury or ligamentous disruption. At C3-4 mild disk bulging seen without spinal stenosis or foraminal narrowing. At C4-5 level lumbar disc bulging with mild to moderate left-sided and mild right-sided foraminal narrowing. At C5-6 level cord disk bulging with mild-to-moderate left foraminal narrowing. No abnormalities from C6-7 through T3-4. The spinal cord shows normal intrinsic signal and no compression.
